content.text:
Let me analyze the structure and provide the solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 6 distinct blocks
- It has 4 layers from bottom to top
- The design appears to be a stylized castle or building with two towers
- Base layer: Red arch block
- Second layer: Green horizontal block
- Third layer: Blue cube block with orange cylinder block beside it
- Fourth layer: Two orange triangular roof pieces

Block Components and Spatial Relationships:
- Bottom: Red arch block (Block #1)
- Middle: Green horizontal rectangular block (Block #11)
- Upper left: Blue cube block (Block #6)
- Upper right: Orange cylindrical block (Block #12)
- Top left: Orange triangular roof (Block #14)
- Top right: Orange triangular roof (Block #14)

Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 11
    Step3: Move block with index 6
    Step4: Move block with index 12
    Step5: Move block with index 14
    Step6: Move block with index 14
}

Note that Block #14 is used twice for the two roof pieces. The blocks are assembled from bottom to top, starting with the foundation arch, then the green platform, followed by the blue cube and orange cylinder towers, and finally topped with the two orange triangular roof pieces.
